    <svcsection id="s05006W" division="TRUCK" formnum="CTS-5160" revno="W" date="01/28/1998">
        <title>POWER STEERING PUMP: EATON MODEL BB135 R, L</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Eaton</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3900</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>GENERAL</title>
                <para>This manual applies to the 3900FC model.</para>
                <para>The Eaton Model BB power steering pump is a hydraulically balanced roll vane assembly with a
                    pressure balanced end plate. The reservoir is mounted on top of the pump body. A filter element is
                    located in the reservoir to remove foreign particles from the fluid.
                </para>
                <para>The power steering pump is either belt or gear driven, depending on engine application used (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0500601">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0500602">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
